    month = feb,
   volume = 53,
    pages = {37-52},
 abstract = "{Recently reported infrared (IR) galaxy number counts and cosmic infrared
background (CIRB) all suggest that galaxies have experienced strong
evolution sometime in their lifetime. We statistically estimate the
galaxy evolution history from these data. We find that an
order-of-magnitude increase of the far-infrared (FIR) luminosity at
